#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:1
msgid "TriplyDB Publishing"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:3
msgid ""
"The editor can publish service metadata directly to a TriplyDB knowledge "
"graph without any manual file handling. The publish feature is available via "
"the **Publish** button in the bottom-right of the application."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:12
msgid "What publishing does"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:14
msgid ""
"When you publish, the editor generates the complete Turtle output for the "
"current service definition and uploads it to the specified TriplyDB dataset "
"via the TriplyDB API. A backend proxy then ensures the data is accessible "
"via a cumulative SPARQL endpoint — so each published service accumulates in "
"the dataset rather than overwriting previous entries."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:16
msgid ""
"Organisation logos, when present, are uploaded as named assets alongside the "
"Turtle data, making them available as linked resources in the knowledge "
"graph."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:20
msgid "Progress tracking"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:22
msgid ""
"The publish dialog shows step-by-step progress with real-time status "
"indicators:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:24
msgid "Validating form"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:25
msgid "Generating TTL"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:26
msgid "Uploading to TriplyDB"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:27
msgid "Updating service via backend proxy"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:29
msgid ""
"Each step transitions from pending to complete as it finishes. On success, "
"the dialog displays a direct link to the published dataset and closes "
"automatically after two seconds. Errors are surfaced inside the dialog with "
"details, and an inline message appears under the page title after the dialog "
"closes."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:33
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:35
msgid ""
"Publishing requires four values: the TriplyDB base URL, account name, "
"dataset name, and an API token. The token is stored in browser localStorage "
"— it is never transmitted to any server other than the configured TriplyDB "
"instance."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:37
msgid ""
"An optional **Test Connection** button verifies credentials before "
"publishing, without uploading any data."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:41
msgid "Cumulative data storage"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Ctriplydb-publishing.md:43
msgid ""
"TriplyDB's default behaviour creates auto-numbered graphs on each upload. "
"The backend proxy addresses this by querying across all graphs and "
"presenting a unified view, so the dataset always appears to contain all "
"published services regardless of how many upload operations have been "
"performed."
msgstr ""
